1
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:42,416
Fall back, fall back,
go! Retreat!

2
00:01:49,166 --> 00:01:50,916
[roars]

3
00:01:58,125 --> 00:02:01,083
[roars]

4
00:02:30,625 --> 00:02:33,875
[SOLDIER 1A] Please, Your
Majesty! You have to flee!

5
00:02:33,958 --> 00:02:36,250
[gasps]

6
00:02:39,041 --> 00:02:41,625
[ANCIENT KING gasps]

7
00:03:00,833 --> 00:03:01,833
[KAISAR]
Yah!

8
00:03:01,916 --> 00:03:03,250
[FAVARO]
Yah!

9
00:03:13,458 --> 00:03:14,708
[KAISAR grunts]

10
00:03:15,416 --> 00:03:16,625
[FAVARO]
Ha!

11
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:18,333
[KAISAR yells]

12
00:03:25,208 --> 00:03:26,500
[laughs]

13
00:03:36,083 --> 00:03:36,875
[grunts]

14
00:03:36,958 --> 00:03:38,083
Heh.

15
00:03:39,708 --> 00:03:42,583
[KAISAR grunts]
Favaro!

16
00:03:50,708 --> 00:03:52,375
[TAVERN GIRLS panting]

17
00:03:52,458 --> 00:03:54,958
[OUTLAW 1A] Quit running,
damn it! Get back here!

18
00:03:55,041 --> 00:03:57,166
[OUTLAW 1B]
We're not done with you!

19
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:00,250
[FAVARO laughs]

20
00:04:01,541 --> 00:04:02,875
[TOWN MAN 1A yelps]

21
00:04:05,458 --> 00:04:07,041
You coward.

22
00:04:10,791 --> 00:04:12,166
Sayonara.

23
00:04:12,250 --> 00:04:14,041
[TOWN WOMEN gasp]

24
00:04:14,125 --> 00:04:15,958
[grunts]

25
00:04:18,208 --> 00:04:20,833
Uh... Heh, heh.

26
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,875
--[whip cracks]
--[horse neighs]

27
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:27,083
[KAISAR grunts]

28
00:04:27,166 --> 00:04:28,791
Whoa, don't do that!

29
00:04:30,750 --> 00:04:32,875
Not funny, man,
I could get hurt!

30
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:36,208
Yep, one of those days.

31
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:40,500
[KAISAR]
Favaro!

32
00:04:41,958 --> 00:04:44,083
Oh! Hey, Kaisar,
welcome aboard!

33
00:04:44,166 --> 00:04:46,333
Steering sucks,
but I love the view!

34
00:04:49,416 --> 00:04:53,000
[TAVERN GIRLS groan, whimper]

35
00:04:53,083 --> 00:04:55,458
[OUTLAW 1A]
You girls are coming with us.

36
00:05:01,333 --> 00:05:02,541
[KAISAR, FAVARO grunting]

37
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:05,000
[FAVARO]
Oh! Nice! Thank you!

38
00:05:12,458 --> 00:05:16,750
Huh. Here ya go sweetie,
from my heart to your lips!

39
00:05:16,833 --> 00:05:18,916
[KAISAR grunts]

40
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:20,541
Your jokes will not save you.

41
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:23,583
[FAVARO] Aw, now you're
just playin' hard to get.

42
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:27,250
Silence, Favaro! All you
speak is nonsense and lies!

43
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:29,916
Your attitude's all wrong.
See, that's your weakness.

44
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:30,625
[grunts]

45
00:05:30,708 --> 00:05:32,583
So focused on one thing.

46
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:33,916
Ya can't see the
bigger picture.

47
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,416
[groans]

48
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:39,791
[sighs] Including what's
right behind you.

49
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:41,500
Oh, well, your loss.

50
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:43,916
[TAVERN GIRL 1A]
No! Let go of me!

51
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:45,125
[TAVERN GIRL 1B]
Help!

52
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:47,125
[OUTLAW 1B] Shut up,
no one's gonna save ya.

53
00:05:47,208 --> 00:05:50,083
[OUTLAW 1C]
Huh? Look! What is that?

54
00:05:50,166 --> 00:05:54,500
[FAVARO] Oh crap, oh crap.
Yep this is happening.

55
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:55,666
[FAVARO screams]

56
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:57,458
Don't like this!

57
00:05:59,166 --> 00:06:03,000
[FAVARO screams]

58
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:05,708
[FAVARO groans]

59
00:06:05,791 --> 00:06:08,083
[OUTLAW 1A]
Hey! Who the hell are you?

60
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:10,958
You come to save them wenches?

61
00:06:11,041 --> 00:06:12,083
They're gone!

62
00:06:12,166 --> 00:06:14,708
You idiot! How'd you
let them get away!

63
00:06:14,791 --> 00:06:17,916
[FAVARO] Sorry, guys,
did I scare off your dates?

64
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:19,208
[OUTLAW 1A]
That bracelet!

65
00:06:19,291 --> 00:06:20,958
[FAVARO]
Huh? Oh, this old thing?

66
00:06:21,041 --> 00:06:22,291
[OUTLAW 1A]
He's a bounty hunter!

67
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,750
[KAISAR]
Favaro!

68
00:06:24,833 --> 00:06:26,416
[OUTLAWS yelp]

69
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,125
[OUTLAW 1A] Now there's
a prince on a white horse?

70
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:32,083
I think we nabbed
the wrong girls.

71
00:06:32,166 --> 00:06:35,625
That's no prince!
That's a bounty hunter, too!

72
00:06:35,708 --> 00:06:36,625
[gasps]

73
00:06:36,708 --> 00:06:38,291
--[FAVARO] Huh?
--[OUTLAWS grunt]

74
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,416
Stop!

75
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:42,750
[OUTLAWS]
Uh...

76
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:45,083
--[FAVARO] Outta the way!
--[TAVERN PATRONS gasping]

77
00:06:47,208 --> 00:06:49,125
[FAVARO] Who brings
a horse into a tavern?

78
00:06:49,208 --> 00:06:50,666
Y'know you're losing
those bounties

79
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:52,583
--while you're chasing me!
--[KAISAR] Silence, dog!

80
00:06:52,666 --> 00:06:54,416
You dare talk to me
about bounty hunting,

81
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:56,291
when you're the only reason
I was forced into this

82
00:06:56,375 --> 00:06:57,500
wretched life to begin with!

83
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:02,291
Right. Pin it all
on me. Real mature!

84
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:03,125
[neighs]

85
00:07:03,208 --> 00:07:04,750
[TAVERN PATRONS gasp]

86
00:07:06,416 --> 00:07:08,958
Wait! You are deplorable!

87
00:07:09,041 --> 00:07:10,000
[growls]

88
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:11,208
[FAVARO]
Eh.

89
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:13,208
[KAISAR] Come back!
Barina Shuttle Lidfard!

90
00:07:13,291 --> 00:07:16,958
Heh. Poor guy. He needs
some friends.

91
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:18,541
Uh-- Ah!

92
00:07:18,625 --> 00:07:19,458
Ah!

93
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:21,083
Now that is the good stuff.

94
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:22,750
Hey!

95
00:07:22,833 --> 00:07:24,333
Don't worry about
your place, buddy,

96
00:07:24,416 --> 00:07:25,875
I'll take care of it.

97
00:07:25,958 --> 00:07:28,208
Frowny guy's bounty'll
cover the repairs.

98
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:34,708
And my large tab.

99
00:07:34,791 --> 00:07:36,041
Are ya serious?

100
00:07:36,125 --> 00:07:38,208
Always.

101
00:07:45,500 --> 00:07:47,000
[OUTLAW 1A]
It ain't good, boys.

102
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:48,416
If we go back empty handed,

103
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:50,458
after taking the
horses out all day...

104
00:07:50,541 --> 00:07:52,375
[OUTLAWS]
Sir Garth will kill us!

105
00:07:52,458 --> 00:07:55,458
--[horses neigh]
--[OUTLAWS yell]

106
00:08:03,541 --> 00:08:04,291
[OUTLAWS groan]

107
00:08:04,375 --> 00:08:05,625
Did the wagon hit somethin'?

108
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:07,750
[OUTLAW 1A]
Look! What's that?

109
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,833
[OUTLAW 1A]
It's a woman!

110
00:08:16,375 --> 00:08:18,166
[OUTLAW 1A] Who are you?
How'd you get up there?

111
00:08:18,250 --> 00:08:21,708
And why are you naked?

112
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:23,250
[OUTLAW 1B]
Did you fall from the sky?

113
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:25,375
[OUTLAW 1C] You idiot, since
when do girls fall from the sky?

114
00:08:25,458 --> 00:08:26,708
[OUTLAW 1B]
Don't you call me an idiot!

115
00:08:26,791 --> 00:08:29,458
[OUTLAW 1A]
Hey! You gonna answer me?

116
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:32,750
[AMIRA] The compass is broken.
I can't find Helheim.

117
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,375
[OUTLAW 1A] What's she
talking about? Ah, who cares!

118
00:08:35,458 --> 00:08:37,250
Boss's gift just
fell in our laps.

119
00:08:37,333 --> 00:08:40,000
Yeah, but I'm thinking she can
fall into our laps first.

120
00:08:40,083 --> 00:08:42,541
[OUTLAWS cackle]

121
00:08:45,125 --> 00:08:46,291
[AMIRA grunts]

122
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:53,416
[GARTH]
I want my girls! Now!

123
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,166
[OUTLAW 1D]
Boss, I heard a bounty hunter

124
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:57,958
was in town this mornin',
causin' all kinds of trouble.

125
00:08:58,041 --> 00:08:58,583
So, I'm thinkin'--

126
00:08:58,666 --> 00:09:00,041
[GARTH growls]

127
00:09:00,125 --> 00:09:02,083
[OUTLAWS whimper]

128
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:05,333
[GARTH] You're gonna bring that
damn bounty hunter to me.

129
00:09:05,416 --> 00:09:06,750
[FAVARO] I'll save you
the trouble, boys!

130
00:09:06,833 --> 00:09:07,791
[OUTLAWS gasp]

131
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:12,250
The damn bounty hunter
just brought himself.

132
00:09:12,333 --> 00:09:14,916
[GARTH] He thinks he's funny.
Tear 'im apart.

133
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,166
Bastard!

134
00:09:16,250 --> 00:09:18,708
[FAVARO, OUTLAWS grunting]

135
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:19,708
[OUTLAW 1E]
Where'd he go?

136
00:09:19,791 --> 00:09:20,375
[OUTLAW 1F]
Huh?

137
00:09:20,458 --> 00:09:20,958
[GARTH]
Look down!

138
00:09:21,041 --> 00:09:21,750
Huh?

139
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:24,458
[FAVARO]
One. Two. Three.

140
00:09:27,750 --> 00:09:29,291
[FAVARO groans]

141
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:30,708
[GARTH]
Not bad, hunter.

142
00:09:30,791 --> 00:09:31,500
[FAVARO]
Huh?

143
00:09:31,583 --> 00:09:34,041
Shabale Seta Ruge.

144
00:09:35,375 --> 00:09:36,458
[FAVARO gasps]

145
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:44,000
A Summoning Spell, huh?
Well, in that case.

146
00:09:45,541 --> 00:09:46,041
[FAVARO yelps]

147
00:09:46,125 --> 00:09:47,666
After him!

148
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:52,000
[FAVARO yelps]

149
00:09:53,041 --> 00:09:54,125
[MONSTERS roar]

150
00:09:54,208 --> 00:09:55,333
What happened to--

151
00:09:55,416 --> 00:09:57,791
[coughs] Blasted dust.

152
00:09:57,875 --> 00:10:00,333
I said what happened to your
jokes and bravado now,

153
00:10:00,416 --> 00:10:01,166
bounty hunter?

154
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,208
I dunno!

155
00:10:02,291 --> 00:10:03,833
But here's an even
better question.

156
00:10:03,916 --> 00:10:05,958
Where'd that big puddle
come from, I don't remember

157
00:10:06,041 --> 00:10:07,833
it raining today, do you?

158
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:12,458
Who the hell cares?
Burn him to a crisp!

159
00:10:21,500 --> 00:10:22,500
What? But how?

160
00:10:22,583 --> 00:10:24,458
[FAVARO]
Oh! Wait! Now! Now I remember!

161
00:10:24,541 --> 00:10:26,291
The plants out here
looked dry but I didn't

162
00:10:26,375 --> 00:10:29,708
have any water, so I gave
'em some alcohol instead.

163
00:10:31,333 --> 00:10:33,916
You bastard! So you knew
about their skill?

164
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,083
About their fire attack?

165
00:10:35,166 --> 00:10:36,166
Yup!

166
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:38,375
Now here's some advice,
free of charge.

167
00:10:38,458 --> 00:10:41,250
Don't have a blabber-mouth
for a pet.

168
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:44,166
[grunts, growls]

169
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,875
Damn you!

170
00:10:47,458 --> 00:10:48,958
[yelps]

171
00:10:50,458 --> 00:10:53,708
[GARTH groans]

172
00:10:53,791 --> 00:10:55,500
Miserable scoundrel.

173
00:10:55,583 --> 00:10:58,625
Well, that's not very nice.
It's not my fault you're clumsy.

174
00:10:58,708 --> 00:11:01,083
Seel Soh Cetom.

175
00:11:04,958 --> 00:11:08,250
Heh. And that makes 20!

176
00:11:16,208 --> 00:11:17,666
[BACCHUS snoring]

177
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:19,000
Wow.

178
00:11:19,083 --> 00:11:21,083
I'm surprised.

179
00:11:21,166 --> 00:11:23,666
[HAMSA] Hey, Bacchus!
Wake up, ya drunk!

180
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:25,041
We've got a visitor!

181
00:11:25,125 --> 00:11:27,750
Huh? Get off
my back, would ya?

182
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,375
Don't you know who
you're talkin' to?

183
00:11:29,458 --> 00:11:31,333
The god of booze hounds, right?

184
00:11:31,416 --> 00:11:33,958
Maybe you should think about
cutting back a little, chief.

185
00:11:34,041 --> 00:11:35,625
It cannot be good
for your health.

186
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:39,000
[FAVARO sighs] Always freaks
me out how much bigger it is

187
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:40,125
on the inside.

188
00:11:40,208 --> 00:11:41,833
Don't come bargin'
in just to complain!

189
00:11:41,916 --> 00:11:43,833
[FAVARO]
Here you go. Prey of the day!

190
00:11:43,916 --> 00:11:45,291
[BACCHUS]
Hm?

191
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:49,083
[BACCHUS]
All right, Puff Ball Head.

192
00:11:49,166 --> 00:11:50,166
Eight hundred Rupies.

193
00:11:50,250 --> 00:11:51,875
[FAVARO]
Would you stop calling me that?

194
00:11:51,958 --> 00:11:53,916
And why are you only
giving me half the reward?

195
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:57,208
Those posters said "1600,"
and yes I can read!

196
00:11:57,291 --> 00:12:00,750
Shut your hole, human,
don't you know who--

197
00:12:02,375 --> 00:12:04,166
Are you gonna puke?

198
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:06,583
Careful. It's a fancy couch.

199
00:12:06,666 --> 00:12:07,708
[FAVARO]
Hup, uh--

200
00:12:07,791 --> 00:12:08,500
[BACCHUS groans]

201
00:12:08,583 --> 00:12:10,125
Are you kidding me?

202
00:12:12,458 --> 00:12:14,625
It's my policy to spend
every Rupie I make

203
00:12:14,708 --> 00:12:16,750
before the next morning.
It's the only way to live!

204
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:17,875
[TAVERN GIRLS giggle]

205
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:19,416
So! Let's drink the
house down, girls!

206
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:22,166
And don't expect to get
any sleep tonight!

207
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:24,166
You must be strong
to capture them.

208
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:27,833
Yeah, I guess. Today was
a milestone for me.

209
00:12:29,125 --> 00:12:30,416
My 200th bounty.

210
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:31,666
[TAVERN GIRL 1C]
That's amazing!

211
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:34,666
So. You must've faced
all sorts of danger.

212
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:35,916
I've battled things
that would make

213
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,458
a pretty lady like you cry.

214
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,125
Exciting, right?

215
00:12:41,208 --> 00:12:43,166
I bet you've seen
beautiful cities, too.

216
00:12:43,250 --> 00:12:47,375
Not as beautiful as
the girls inside them.

217
00:12:47,458 --> 00:12:48,583
Girls like you.

218
00:12:48,666 --> 00:12:49,500
[TAVERN GIRL 1C]
All you talk about is women.

219
00:12:49,583 --> 00:12:50,750
[FAVARO]
That's right!

220
00:12:50,833 --> 00:12:52,791
Women are the best gods
and worst demons, too!

221
00:12:52,875 --> 00:12:55,041
I won't stop 'til I've
drunk with 'em all!

222
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,791
That's why I'm going
back to Helheim!

223
00:12:56,875 --> 00:12:57,833
--[AMIRA gasps]
--[TAVERN GIRL 1A] Where?

224
00:12:57,916 --> 00:12:59,625
[FAVARO]
Helheim, my next stop!

225
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:01,041
Oh, is that a place?

226
00:13:01,125 --> 00:13:03,000
Well, yeah. You never
heard of it?

227
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:04,291
I've heard of it.

228
00:13:04,375 --> 00:13:06,500
Heard it's covered in
snow and ice so cold,

229
00:13:06,583 --> 00:13:07,833
it can freeze ya
where ya stand.

230
00:13:07,916 --> 00:13:10,166
Yeah, that's right!
It's not for the weak!

231
00:13:10,250 --> 00:13:12,500
That's if you can even survive
the journey, of course--

232
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,625
I can't tell ya how many
warriors and bounty hunters

233
00:13:14,708 --> 00:13:16,458
have lost their lives just
tryin' to get there!

234
00:13:16,541 --> 00:13:17,583
[TAVERN GIRLS]
Scary!

235
00:13:17,666 --> 00:13:19,083
It's really no problem
for me, though.

236
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:20,375
I'll get there fine!

237
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:22,916
'Cause I know
a special shortcut!

238
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:27,125
A Helheim shortcut?
That's perfect.

239
00:13:27,208 --> 00:13:28,791
[KAISAR grunts]

240
00:13:28,875 --> 00:13:30,458
[KAISAR]
Forgive me.

241
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:35,166
Hm. Unusual design.
Are you a foreigner?

242
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,625
Well, if you're lost,
it would be my honor

243
00:13:39,708 --> 00:13:41,250
to show you around.

244
00:13:41,333 --> 00:13:44,375
Thanks, but there's no need.
I've chosen my guide.

245
00:13:44,458 --> 00:13:45,541
[gasps]

246
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:47,333
[FAVARO laughing]

247
00:13:47,416 --> 00:13:48,500
[KAISAR growls]

248
00:13:48,583 --> 00:13:50,166
[FAVARO laughing]

249
00:13:51,833 --> 00:13:53,791
Hey, pal. Took ya long enough.

250
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:56,625
Ladies, meet Pompadorable.
D'ya find your horse?

251
00:13:56,708 --> 00:13:57,958
My name is Kaisar!

252
00:13:58,041 --> 00:14:00,875
[FAVARO] Ah... I'll take
that freak-out as a "no."

253
00:14:00,958 --> 00:14:02,541
Too bad, I hear
he's a good horse.

254
00:14:02,625 --> 00:14:03,750
[KAISAR]
Yes.

255
00:14:03,833 --> 00:14:06,583
Barina Shuttle Lidfard
is a great horse.

256
00:14:06,666 --> 00:14:09,875
He was all that remained
of my family fortune.

257
00:14:09,958 --> 00:14:11,916
Now you've robbed
me of him, too!

258
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,500
[TAVERN GIRLS gasp]

259
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:16,291
[KAISAR grunts]
I'll kill you!

260
00:14:16,375 --> 00:14:18,208
Aw, relax, would ya?

261
00:14:18,291 --> 00:14:20,958
Life's too short for this
grudge crap. Everyone!

262
00:14:21,041 --> 00:14:23,916
This guy's way more rich and
loose with his coins than me.

263
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,333
Cozy up to barret
head and you'll be

264
00:14:25,416 --> 00:14:27,416
--drinkin' for free all night!
--[KAISAR] Wait, what?

265
00:14:27,500 --> 00:14:28,458
[TAVERN GIRL 1C]
Hey, handsome.

266
00:14:28,541 --> 00:14:29,541
[TAVERN GIRL 1B]
Hey, cutie.

267
00:14:29,625 --> 00:14:30,666
You should come
have a drink with us.

268
00:14:30,750 --> 00:14:32,166
I'm sorry, but I can't.

269
00:14:32,250 --> 00:14:35,083
Oh. Just look at
that strong chin. Ah.

270
00:14:35,166 --> 00:14:37,250
You must be a knight,
I can tell.

271
00:14:37,333 --> 00:14:39,791
They're always the sexy ones.

272
00:14:39,875 --> 00:14:40,875
You ladies are far too kind.

273
00:14:40,958 --> 00:14:43,458
[TAVERN GIRLS sigh]

274
00:14:43,541 --> 00:14:45,625
[TAVERN GIRL 1A] Can I
play with your barrettes?

275
00:14:45,708 --> 00:14:47,625
[TAVERN GIRL 1B]
Can you show us your sword?

276
00:14:47,708 --> 00:14:49,625
[TAVERN GIRL 1C]
I get to sit in his lap first!

277
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:52,416
[KAISAR]
Favaro!

278
00:14:54,958 --> 00:14:58,000
Honestly. That guy
never gives up.

279
00:14:58,083 --> 00:15:00,250
He's really gotta get
himself a new hobby.

280
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:01,625
Or a girl. Or three.

281
00:15:01,708 --> 00:15:02,791
[AMIRA]
You there.

282
00:15:02,875 --> 00:15:04,791
What the hell, man,
give me some space!

283
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:06,833
Can't you see
I'm tryin' to piss?

284
00:15:06,916 --> 00:15:08,458
Hm?

285
00:15:08,541 --> 00:15:11,916
Hold on, that is
definitely not a guy.

286
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,416
That's weird.

287
00:15:13,500 --> 00:15:15,791
Why are you dressed up
like one, then?

288
00:15:15,875 --> 00:15:18,083
You just into that kinda' thing?

289
00:15:18,166 --> 00:15:19,416
Not a deal breaker, though.

290
00:15:19,500 --> 00:15:20,750
So.

291
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,416
Is it true that you know
of a shortcut to Helheim?

292
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,458
What?

293
00:15:23,541 --> 00:15:25,041
I heard you say
that at the tavern.

294
00:15:25,125 --> 00:15:27,000
[FAVARO]
Ohhh. I get it.

295
00:15:27,083 --> 00:15:29,250
She heard me spinning one
of my little stories, huh?

296
00:15:29,333 --> 00:15:31,916
Please tell me.
I must get to Helheim.

297
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,500
Do you know the way? I'm lost.

298
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:35,541
[FAVARO] Okay...
How should I play this?

299
00:15:35,625 --> 00:15:39,125
Keep making stuff up,
or run for it?

300
00:15:39,208 --> 00:15:41,083
Are you listening to me?

301
00:15:41,166 --> 00:15:43,208
[FAVARO]
Or I could...

302
00:15:43,291 --> 00:15:44,375
Yep, that's it.

303
00:15:44,458 --> 00:15:46,208
Oh, sure, I practically
blazed the trail.

304
00:15:46,291 --> 00:15:48,541
But I can't tell ya
just 'cause you asked.

305
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:49,375
Nothin's free, dear.

306
00:15:49,458 --> 00:15:50,625
Then what do you want?

307
00:15:50,708 --> 00:15:52,541
That's a great question!

308
00:15:52,625 --> 00:15:56,333
What I want is pretty
simple. It's love.

309
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:57,041
Love?

310
00:15:57,125 --> 00:15:59,125
Yes. Romantic, right?

311
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:03,625
Love from a beautiful girl.
In one passionate kissy-kiss!

312
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:06,083
A kiss? From me?

313
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,458
[GHOS]
There you are!

314
00:16:07,541 --> 00:16:09,375
[FAVARO growls]
The hell, man?

315
00:16:09,458 --> 00:16:11,208
Things were just
starting to get good!

316
00:16:11,291 --> 00:16:14,750
Seriously, Kaisar, you are
a monumental pain in the--

317
00:16:14,833 --> 00:16:16,333
Uh. What?

318
00:16:16,416 --> 00:16:17,333
[GHOS GIRL laughs]

319
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:17,916
Who're you?

320
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:19,250
The name's Ghos.

321
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:20,833
And you're gonna suffer
for what you did

322
00:16:20,916 --> 00:16:21,791
to my kid brother, Garth!

323
00:16:21,875 --> 00:16:25,083
Ghos? Kid brother? Hang on.

324
00:16:28,416 --> 00:16:29,791
Oh, I get it!

325
00:16:29,875 --> 00:16:32,500
So that's why Bacchus only
paid me half of the bounty!

326
00:16:32,583 --> 00:16:33,958
Listen.

327
00:16:34,041 --> 00:16:36,166
I don't have time for this,
just tell me the way to--

328
00:16:36,250 --> 00:16:37,916
Hold your horses, honey.

329
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:40,458
I gotta take care of some
unfinished business here.

330
00:16:40,541 --> 00:16:42,541
And then, we'll get
back to that kiss.

331
00:16:42,625 --> 00:16:45,166
Fool! The only thing
you'll be kissing...

332
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:47,333
...is your ass goodbye!

333
00:16:57,125 --> 00:16:59,291
[roars]

334
00:17:01,708 --> 00:17:03,250
You're joking, right?

335
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,166
You think you can scare me
with that puny thing?

336
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:08,541
Your kid brother could
summon way better than...

337
00:17:12,041 --> 00:17:13,000
Nevermind!

338
00:17:13,083 --> 00:17:16,125
Tear him apart,
one limb at a time!

339
00:17:16,208 --> 00:17:18,416
[FAVARO grunting]

340
00:17:20,708 --> 00:17:23,208
You got some serious
power there, bud!

341
00:17:23,291 --> 00:17:25,375
You should get work
as a castle crusher!

342
00:17:31,625 --> 00:17:33,416
[FAVARO yelps]

343
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:35,916
[FAVARO grunts]

344
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,625
[FAVARO yells]

345
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:39,791
[MONSTER groans]

346
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:41,958
[FAVARO yelping]

347
00:17:42,041 --> 00:17:43,666
[FAVARO grunts]

348
00:17:43,750 --> 00:17:45,291
Big bastard.

349
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:48,791
[FAVARO]
My sword!

350
00:17:51,291 --> 00:17:53,625
[FAVARO] Run, you idiot!
You'll get killed!

351
00:17:53,708 --> 00:17:55,708
You can't be my guide
if you're dead.

352
00:17:55,791 --> 00:17:57,208
[FAVARO]
Huh?

353
00:17:57,291 --> 00:18:01,375
[AMIRA] Stay back and find
some cover. I'll handle this.

354
00:18:06,416 --> 00:18:07,208
[gasps]

355
00:18:07,291 --> 00:18:09,791
[growls]

356
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:32,500
The hell?

357
00:18:32,583 --> 00:18:35,958
[gasps] She's a demon?

358
00:18:40,041 --> 00:18:42,666
[MONSTER groans]

359
00:18:56,375 --> 00:18:57,250
[GHOS]
Huh?

360
00:19:06,791 --> 00:19:08,833
[gasps, groans]

361
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:10,916
Tch.

362
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:15,083
[GHOS groans]
You bastard. You fight dirty.

363
00:19:19,416 --> 00:19:21,666
Making that mountain-sized
demon look tiny

364
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:24,458
at first was a way
dirtier trick, in my book.

365
00:19:24,541 --> 00:19:27,375
So. You two come as a package?

366
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:29,500
[GHOS GIRLS gasp, scream]

367
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:32,583
Aw, come on, I haven't
done anything yet!

368
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:44,083
[FAVARO]
Ugh. That was close.

369
00:19:44,166 --> 00:19:45,916
[FAVARO groans]

370
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,916
Spoke too soon.

371
00:19:55,833 --> 00:19:58,708
[FAVARO pants]
A demon?

372
00:19:58,791 --> 00:20:05,000
[FAVARO chuckles]

373
00:20:05,083 --> 00:20:07,916
Seein' things.

374
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,083
This is where I realize
I have a drinking problem.

375
00:20:28,583 --> 00:20:30,041
[gasps]

376
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:50,375
[FAVARO gasps]

377
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:03,500
[yelps]

378
00:21:03,583 --> 00:21:07,125
[panting]

379
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:12,791
Jeez. Crazy dream.

380
00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:15,416
Oh. You're finally up.
About time.

381
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,958
[FAVARO]
Where am I?

382
00:21:17,041 --> 00:21:18,750
[TAVERN GIRL 1A]
You're in the tavern's attic.

383
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:21,125
Found you on the ground outside.

384
00:21:21,208 --> 00:21:24,875
Hauling you up here was no
easy task, I'll have you know.

385
00:21:24,958 --> 00:21:26,375
Don't you remember?

386
00:21:26,458 --> 00:21:28,541
Huh...

387
00:21:28,625 --> 00:21:30,166
Oh...

388
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:33,208
Heh. I guess I had too much
of that ale and blacked out.

389
00:21:33,291 --> 00:21:36,125
Had some weird dreams, too.

390
00:21:36,208 --> 00:21:38,083
Well, I ran a bath
for you, earlier.

391
00:21:38,166 --> 00:21:39,708
You should splash water
on your face.

392
00:21:39,791 --> 00:21:41,208
Yeah, thanks.

393
00:21:41,291 --> 00:21:43,916
Maybe I'll wash the rest
of me while I'm at it.

394
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,208
[gasps]

395
00:21:56,291 --> 00:21:58,041
[whimpers]

396
00:21:58,125 --> 00:22:00,500
[FAVARO] Not the reaction
I usually get, but uh.

397
00:22:00,583 --> 00:22:01,666
Heh. I'll take it.

398
00:22:01,750 --> 00:22:03,666
[TAVERN GIRL 1A]
That's... That's a tail!

399
00:22:03,750 --> 00:22:06,291
[FAVARO]
Wow. Uh, thanks, I guess?

400
00:22:06,375 --> 00:22:08,916
[screams] Demon!

401
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:10,416
